    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2522456492" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2522456492" />
    <a title="Monica Reents" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13910930-monica-reents"><img alt="Monica Reents" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525921392p2/13910930.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2522456492?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Monica Reents" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Monica Reents" href="/user/show/13910930-monica-reents">Monica Reents</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/41311403-love-is-the-answer-god-is-the-cure">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2522456492" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13091809571716680514">Aimee Cabo Nikolov has written a book that is ultimately a story of inspiration. The author shares the events of her life, a life that has been wrought with abuse, addiction, and turmoil. She writes about the balance she created between good and evil, by sharing her faith in God and the love in her heart.<br/><br/>There were moments that forced me to set the book down and just soak in what I had read, amazed by her determination to be a survivor, while feeling shocked by the amount of sexual, emotional, a</span>
  <span id="freeText13091809571716680514" style="display:none">Aimee Cabo Nikolov has written a book that is ultimately a story of inspiration. The author shares the events of her life, a life that has been wrought with abuse, addiction, and turmoil. She writes about the balance she created between good and evil, by sharing her faith in God and the love in her heart.<br /><br />There were moments that forced me to set the book down and just soak in what I had read, amazed by her determination to be a survivor, while feeling shocked by the amount of sexual, emotional, and mental abuse she endured, not to mention being neglected and, essentially, abandoned. The one person who should have put her arms around Aimee, who should have protected her from predators, like her stepfather, was just another person on the list of people who have deeply hurt her. Her mother chose to stand against Aimee, this I will never understand. As a mother, I wanted to reach into the book many times and pull her out, into safety.<br /><br />Each chapter begins with a prayer, giving the reader insight into the strength of her beliefs, she does not hold back in allowing us into her life and who she really is as she maneuvers her way through one obstacle after another. My heart goes out to her. It is no wonder that addiction became part of her journey, she was searching for a way to numb herself. She has come out of the darkness and beaten evil countless times. She has had to fight for everything her whole life. And while most people would become tired of trying so hard, just to get pushed back down, Aimee shows that it can be done, you can win. Through love.<br /><br />The author writes with an honesty that I am grateful for, because it is those details that allow me, as a reader, to understand the why’s, what’s, and how’s of her life. We are shown how strong her faith and love is, that her heart is in the center of all that she does. She has worked so hard to build her life and family. A little spoiler: she finds her happiness.<br /><br />I was contacted by Aimee Cabo Nikolov and asked to read and review her book. I always feel honored when an author asks me to do this. Regardless of how I found this book, I will never forget Aimee’s story. It is powerful and heart-wrenching and inspirational. To know what she has survived to get where she is now, should give everyone hope for a better future. I would say this as an adult/mature audience book due to some slightly graphic details, but I would absolutely recommend this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13091809571716680514" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

