<div id="review_2543990789" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2543990789" />
    <a title="Lust for Lit" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/74624063-lust-for-lit"><img alt="Lust for Lit" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1512485063p2/74624063.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2543990789?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lust for Lit" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lust for Lit" href="/user/show/74624063-lust-for-lit">Lust for Lit</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/41128585-love-is-the-answer-god-is-the-cure">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2543990789" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2042861499851431175">I&apos;m not sure how to describe &apos;Love is the Answer, God is the Cure&apos;. It is a memoir that will break your heart and sob uncontrollably, whilst also filling you will with hope and marvel at the strength of the human spirit. Aimie Cabo recounts the harrowing story of her life from nightmarish sexual abuse at the hands of her parents, addiction, and poverty. When there was no other comfort for her, she found God – her love for him helped her to find love for others and receive love in return. However</span>
  <span id="freeText2042861499851431175" style="display:none">I'm not sure how to describe 'Love is the Answer, God is the Cure'. It is a memoir that will break your heart and sob uncontrollably, whilst also filling you will with hope and marvel at the strength of the human spirit. Aimie Cabo recounts the harrowing story of her life from nightmarish sexual abuse at the hands of her parents, addiction, and poverty. When there was no other comfort for her, she found God – her love for him helped her to find love for others and receive love in return. However, there was more tragedy to come, when her daughter was brutally attacked by a Craig's List tenant. <br /><br />This is the remarkable story of a remarkable family. Whereas tragedy often has the ability to drive families apart, this family has such an extraordinary bond, that they have weathered storms that would destroy so many others. You don't need to be a believer in God to relate to Aimie and her family's strength. They drew their power and inspiration from their faith in God, but it shows that you don't need to get pulled down by past tragedies, you can find a way out of it, with the help of God or in other ways.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2042861499851431175" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


